<br>
When I'm on my cleric and working on tradeskills, I know that buff could help me -- so if I see an enchanter in the zone I find them, try to see if they are busy, send a polite request, offer payment -- and still feel a little cheesy about it.  <br>
<br>
I can't imagine myself ever saying to another player &quot;give me X, Y, or Z&quot; like it's some kind of entitlement.  <br>
<br>
Sharmila <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usalenie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salenie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/19/01 10:15:51 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.zipcon.net/~brus/Salenie_headshot.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: abusive beggers...</span><hr size=1> Gah!  Demanding buffs is definitely getting worse.  I feel really sorry for the ones who can do it.<br>
<br>
I'm a magician but if you're a high elf in a robe, you can cast clarity (and/or (yes &quot;and&quot; sometimes!) port).  I've seen it gone from &quot;Can I have clarity please?&quot; to &quot;Clarity plz?&quot; to &quot;Clarity me.&quot;  I've also gotten tells with stuff that might be requests for buffs like &quot;clr m&quot;, but I don't speak l33t so I ignore those.<br>
<br>
On a side note, one thing I did that helped with the requests is set my inspect text to:  No, I am not an enchater -- I cannot give you clarity.&quot;  Deflects about 50% of the requests.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Remember when running up an examining somone was considered rude too?  :P<br>
<br>
Side note #2:  Most annoying begging I've had to date was for me as a magician in fact.<br>
<br>
Beggar_01 shouts, &quot;Anyone have any arrows I can borrow.&quot;<br>
/tell beggar_01 &quot;I can summon you a couple stack of arrows...they'll rot when you camp and they aren't the greatest stats but they are good enough for practice.  Come to circle if you want them.&quot;<br>
Beggar_01 tells you, &quot;k&quot;<br>
<br>
Waiting for a port, so I make him a nice little treat...10 slot bag, stack of food, stack of drink, stack of bandages, and 7 stacks of arrows.  All summoned so just mana so what the heck.  Hand it off.<br>
<br>
Beggar_01 tells you, &quot;Can I also have three more of these bags, one filled with bandages, one with arrows, but leave the third empty for my loot.  But I don't want more food or water.&quot;<br>
<br>
No thank you, no please.  My ride was incoming and at that point what he was asking for would have taken 16 castings.  so I tell him, &quot;Sorry, I'm just leaving now I don't have time.&quot;<br>
<br>
Beggar_01 tells you, &quot;k&quot;<br>
<br>
Must...not...train...noobs... <p>Salenie Mithrilweaver<BR>Proud Member of <a href=" http://www.clanbattleaxe.com">Clan Battle Axe</a> 



</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udhariana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dhariana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/19/01 10:27:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: abusive beggers...</span><hr size=1> Beggars piss me off to no end!  What's the worst is that my little brother started playing and I realized HE was a beggar.  I wanted to beat him!!  I tried so hard to get him to stop, but he got so much good stuff from it that there was no way he was going to stop.  In fact, he's 8 levels lower than me now, has about 4 times the money I do, and a hell of a lot better gear than I do.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> And has anyone else noted how beggers can't even type correctly? &quot;Hi, do u have extra geer I coold have?&quot; <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I think the main reason this happens is because good majority of the beggars are younger people.  Adults are usually too damn prideful for this stuff.  Kids don't care just so long as they get stuff.  My brother that I mentioned is a classic example.  He was 12 when he started playing.  And before some of you freak out...no, I'm not saying all young people are beggars, nor am I saying that no beggars are adults.  It's just so frustrating!  I look at myself, and have never begged for anything in my life and the only time I've asked for buffs is when the person has offered, or they were people I knew already.  I remember going into Blackburrow one day from Everfrost and some random guy just walks right up to me and asks me to PL him.  I was astonished!  The worst is when they ask for money and you truly are broke or they ask for buffs you don't have and don't believe you when you tell them such.  I had some newbie shouting across the zone what a bitch I was because I wouldn't give him a dmg shield when I repeatedly tried to tell him I couldn't cast that spell for another 4 levels he went off about how I was lying and how I had cast it on him earlier that day.  Freaking psychos I swear!  Anyway, enough ranting on this...it's just making me more and more angry <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
